<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-644-463  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 644 463.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>EDGE on andamp; about ATandamp;T  Nov 26, 1990 v5 n122 p11(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT EDGE Publishing 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Generosity: ATandamp;T will provide U.S. military personnel stationed inSaudi Arabia free calls to the States from Nov. 20-27.andM;</TITLE><DESCRIPT>Company:   American Telephone and Telegraph Co. (Public relations).andO;Ticker:    T.andO;Topic:     Public RelationsInternational CommunicationsDonationTelephone CompaniesTelecommunications ServicesSaudi ArabiaMilitaryLong-Distance Telephone Services.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>ATandamp;T will provide U.S.andP;  military personnel stationed in Saudi Arabia freecalls back to the states from Nov. 20 to 27 to allow them to shareThanksgiving with friends and family.andM;Each service person in Saudi Arabia will be given the opportunity to make onethree-minute ATandamp;T USADirect Service call during the seven-day period.andM;By dialing 1-800-100 from virtually any phone in Saudi Arabia or by using oneof the special telephones ATandamp;T has installed there, U.S.andP;  service people willbe connected directly to an ATandamp;T operator in the United States who cancomplete calls anywhere in the United States, including Puerto Rico.andM;During a free call offer from ATandamp;T in early October, military personnelplaced 135,000 calls through USADirect Service to the United States.andP;  Toaccommodate the expected increase in volume, ATandamp;T last week dramaticallyincreased the number of circuits available for USADirect Service from SaudiArabia.andM;The free Thanksgiving USADirect Service is one part of ATandamp;T's commitment toAmericans stationed abroad.andP;  The company added $500,000 in August to itsannual commitment of $1 million to support USO activities in the gulf such asrecreational centers and tours, including one by Jay Leno this week.andM;Since September, ATandamp;T has transmitted more than 250,000 free facsimiles fromfriends and family to U.S.andP;  service personnel in the Middle East through itsDesert Fax program.andM;Numbers to reach USADirect Service vary by country.andP;  In some countries, theservice is available from specially designated telephones.andP;  For furtherinformation about USADirect Service, call 800/874-4000.andM;Key Executive: Frank Ianna, vp, international marketing.andO;</TEXT></DOC>